Created new branch docs/sangshuduo/TD-12520-docker-doc in taosdata/TDengine

Thanks for your question. Yes, it's possible. You can run taosd and taosAdapter in two different pods and make sure the pod runs taosAdapter installed libtaos.so with the same version of the taosd. An easier way is to install the TDengine server standard package but don't run taosd but just run taosAdapter. And fill the taos client configuration file with your taosd's host. Please let us know what else we can help.

How can I install qpdf on Mac 10.8.3?
MacPorts can help you. Download MacPorts from http://www.macports.org/ and run sudo port install qpdf.
how to specify header file and library path when building a go program which import a cgo package?

I have a simple go program named A and it needs to import a cgo project named B as a module. B needs to include a header file and link a shared object. The header file and shared object are not standard paths (/usr/include, /usr/lib) but in a work directory compiled manually. How I can run go build in A's source directory but specify header/so file path for B? I need to use CMake to do it. Appreciated it if someone can help. Thanks,
why rustc compile complain my simple code "the trait std::io::Read is not implemented for Result<File, anyhow::Error>"

Sorry for my noob rust question. I'm working on a project regarding avro file manipulation tool based on avrow. I see the popular compile error happen on header reading. I see avrow_cli works good but I don't understand why avrow_cli handles that well. Could someone please point out what's wrong? Thank you.
